Sacyr May Earn $31 Million a Year From Panama Canal, Cinco Says

-- B y   B e n   S i l l s
-- 
2011-04-20T06:25:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/sacyr-may-earn-31-million-a-year-from-panama-canal-cinco-says.html
Sacyr Vallehermosa SA may earn
$30.9 million a year over the five-year contract for expanding
the Panama Canal, Cinco Dias reported, citing people close to
the Panamanian government without naming them.   The project, in which Sacyr owns a 48 percent stake, may
earn $322 million before interest, tax, depreciation and
amortization over the period, giving it a 10 percent profit
margin, the newspaper said.   The company is assuming it will have a margin of at least 6
percent, the newspaper said, citing people in the industry. It
said that Sacyr declined to comment.   Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
